3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 39A IS CREATED TO
5 READ AS FOLLOWS:
6 (1) As used in this section:
7 (a) "Declaration" means the Presidential Declaration of a Major Disaster,
8 designated FEMA-4860-DR-KY;
9 (b) "Kentucky disaster" means the severe storms, straight-line winds, flooding,
10 and landslides that occurred in Kentucky beginning on February 14, 2025,
11 as named in the declaration; and
12 (c) "SAFE 4860 fund" means the State Aid Funding for Emergencies 4860
13 fund established in subsection (2) of this section.
14 (2) The State Aid Funding for Emergencies 4860 fund is established and shall be:
15 (a) Administered by the Department of Military Affairs, Division of Emergency
16 Management, in accordance with this section; and
17 (b) A separate fund to provide financial support for those directly impacted by
18 the Kentucky disaster.
19 (3) (a) The SAFE 4860 fund may receive state appropriations, gifts, grants, federal
20 funds, and any other funds, both public and private.
21 (b) Notwithstanding KRS 45.229, moneys in the SAFE 4860 fund shall not
22 lapse and shall carry forward until June 30, 2028.
23 (c) Any interest earnings of the SAFE 4860 fund shall become a part of the
24 fund and shall not lapse.
25 (4) The Department of Military Affairs or the Division of Emergency Management
26 shall not publicly advertise or solicit contributions from the general public that
27 could potentially impact fundraising efforts of nonprofit disaster relief agencies.
